Enum TimeElement.SCALE

    TimeElement

    public static enum TimeElement.SCALE
extends java.lang.Enum<TimeElement.SCALE>
    The set of available time scales for input dates. Note TimeScale class provides methods to transform other time scales (TCB, TCG, TAI) to one of these.

      • LOCAL_TIME

        public static final TimeElement.SCALE LOCAL_TIME
        ID Constant for obtaining Julian day in Local Time.

      • UNIVERSAL_TIME_UT1

        public static final TimeElement.SCALE UNIVERSAL_TIME_UT1
        Universal Time (UT1) ID constant for the time scale. UTC is the common scale given in hour signals, and differs from UT1 by as much as one second. UT1 is the scale commonly used in astronomical calculations. Correction from UTC-UT1 difference is applied when necessary, depending on the last time the file IERS_EOP.txt was updated. If there is no information available, then it will be supposed to be equal: UT1 = UTC. This happends before 1960 and always also in the future.

      • UNIVERSAL_TIME_UTC

        public static final TimeElement.SCALE UNIVERSAL_TIME_UTC
        Universal Time Coordinate ID constant for the time scale. UTC is the common scale given in hour signals, and differs from UT1 by as much as one second. Correction from UTC-UT1 difference is applied, depending on the last time the file IERS_EOP.txt was updated. If there is no information available, then it will be supposed to be equal: UT1 = UTC.

      • TERRESTRIAL_TIME

        public static final TimeElement.SCALE TERRESTRIAL_TIME
        ID Constant for obtaining Julian day in Terrestrial Time.

      • BARYCENTRIC_DYNAMICAL_TIME

        public static final TimeElement.SCALE BARYCENTRIC_DYNAMICAL_TIME
        ID Constant for obtaining Julian day in Barycentric Dynamical Time. This time scale is only dependent on the gravitational potential of the Earth, and it is also called Teph (the time scale of the JPL ephemerides). To obtain the barycentric coordinate time, independent of any potentials in the Solar System, use TimeScale.getTCBminusTDB(double).
